erically. For graphene with\nvacancy disorder, we show that the proposed scaling function of localization\nlength also applies. Lastly, we discuss some ambiguities in calculating the\nsemiclassical conductivity around the charge neutrality point due to the\npresence of resonant states.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Oct 2013 09:01:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Apr 2014 13:40:03 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 30 Jun 2014 11:18:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-01"}
